      "instruction": "VEGGIES: Halve or quarter 1 pound of Brussels sprouts (I quartered bigger ones and halved smaller ones). Peel and core an apple and cut it up in thick slices. Apple slices will cook much faster than other elements of this dish and you want them to be sizeable to get a good texture. Place Brussels Sprouts and apples in a large bowl, add 2 tablespoons of olive oil and 2 sprigs of fresh thyme, stripped from the stem and shake. Or, instead of adding them to a bowl, you can add them to the baking sheet, drizzle olive oil and sprinkle with thyme."
